{"word":"ἄτρυτος","slug":"ἄτρυτος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄτρυτος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:τρύω'><el>τρύω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>not worn away, untiring, unwearied</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>: <i>indefatigable</i>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of things, <i>unabating</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Moschus'>Mosch.</a></b>; of a road, <i>wearisome</i>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}